  "prompt": "What are the best biographies about Bruce Lee?",
  "response": "There are several biographies about Bruce Lee that offer insightful perspectives on his life, philosophy, and impact on martial arts and pop culture. Here are some of the best:\n\n1. **\"Bruce Lee: A Life\" by Matthew Polly** - This comprehensive biography is one of the most detailed works about Lee's life. Polly conducted extensive research and interviews, providing a thorough look at both his personal and professional journey.\n\n2. **\"Bruce Lee: The Man Only I Knew\" by Linda Lee Cadwell** - Written by Bruce Lee's widow, this book offers a personal account of his life and their life together, filled with intimate anecdotes and reflections.\n\n3. **\"Bruce Lee: Fighting Spirit\" by Bruce Thomas** - This biography combines the story of Bruce Lee's life with insights into his martial arts philosophy and contributions to cinema and culture.\n\n4. **\"The Warrior Within: The Philosophies of Bruce Lee\" by John Little** - While not a traditional biography, this book delves into Lee's philosophies and thoughts on martial arts, offering a deeper understanding of his mindset and teachings.\n\n5. **\"Bruce Lee: The Celebrated Life of the Golden Dragon\" by Carrie B. N. Lee (edited by Josephine Lee)** - This biography presents illustrations and personal anecdotes that celebrate his life, making it accessible and visually engaging.\n\n6. **\"The Bruce Lee Letters: A Personal Journey\" by Bruce Lee** - This collection of letters offers a unique glimpse into Lee's thoughts and relationships over the years, providing a more personal touch to his biography.\n\nEach of these works contributes to understanding Bruce Lee's legacy as a martial artist, actor, and cultural icon.",
